content: Some users whom you want to mention don't have access to the room: {{users}}

comment.text: This translation key is used to display a message indicating that some users do not have access to a room. The message appears when users are unable to edit or view content in a specific file (useEditorEvents.ts) and shows a list of non-privileged users who should be mentioned, if any exist.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The phrase 'whom you want to mention' is translated as 'الذين تريد ذكرهم'. While technically correct, a more natural and idiomatic phrasing in Arabic would be 'الذين ترغب بذكرهم' or 'الذين تود ذكرهم'. The current translation sounds slightly formal and less conversational.
The English phrase "mention" is not accurately translated. "Qeyd etmək" implies a note or record, not the act of mentioning someone.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider using a phrase like "sözügedən" or "haqqında danışmaq istəyirsiniz" to better convey the meaning of 'mention'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The English term "access" is translated as "girişi". While technically correct, a more natural and contextually appropriate translation might be "hüququ" (right/permission).
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider using "hüququ" instead of "girişi" to mean 'access'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Някои потребители, които искате да споменете, нямат достъп до стаята: {{users}}' is a literal translation and sounds unnatural in Bulgarian. A more natural phrasing would be 'Има потребители, които искате да споменете, но нямат достъп до стаята: {{users}}' or 'Някои от потребителите, които искате да споменете, нямат достъп до стаята: {{users}}'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Някои от потребителите, които искате да споменете, нямат достъп до стаята: {{users}}

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Joillakin käyttäjillä, jotka haluat mainita, ei ole pääsyä huoneeseen: {{users}}' is a literal translation but sounds awkward in Finnish. A more natural phrasing would be something like 'Osa käyttäjistä, joita haluat mainita, ei ole huoneessa: {{users}}' or '{{users}} -käyttäjillä ei ole pääsyä huoneeseen.'. The original phrasing 'whom you want to mention' isn't perfectly conveyed.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Osa käyttäjistä, joita haluat mainita, ei ole huoneessa: {{users}}

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The English phrase 'whom you want to mention' is not accurately translated. 'Ցանկանում եք նշել' implies a more formal 'you want to indicate' rather than a casual 'you want to mention'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Որոշ օգտատերեր, ովքեր ուզում եք հիշատակել, մուտք չունեն սենյակ. {{users}}

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The use of 'ովքեր' is more grammatically correct for the relative pronoun referring back to users, especially when 'ցանկանում եք' is used.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Որոշ օգտատերեր, ովքեր ուզում եք հիշատակել, մուտք չունեն սենյակ. {{users}}

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The phrase "言及したいユーザー" (people you want to mention) is a bit awkward in this context. A more natural phrasing would be something like "招待したいユーザー" (users you want to invite) or "共有したいユーザー" (users you want to share with). The current translation implies you're explicitly mentioning them for a purpose other than access.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: 言及したいユーザー -> 招待したいユーザー or 共有したいユーザー

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The phrase "whom you want to mention" is not the most natural or accurate translation of "you want to mention". A better phrasing would emphasize the intended meaning of mentioning someone.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ຜູ້​ໃຊ້​ບາງ​ຄົນ​ທີ່​ທ່ານ​ຢາກ​ຊີ້​ສະ​ແດງ​ຊື່​ບໍ່​ມີ​ການ​ເຂົ້າ​ເຖິງ​ຫ້ອງ: {{users}}

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While "ກ່າວ​ເຖິງ" technically means 'to mention', it's somewhat formal and less common in everyday Lao. A more natural phrasing would be 'ຊີ້ສະແດງຊື່' (to indicate the name).
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ປ່ຽນ 'ກ່າວ​ເຖິງ' ເປັນ 'ຊີ້​ສະ​ແດງ​ຊື່'

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The English phrase "whom you want to mention" is not accurately translated. "Kurus vēlaties pieminēt" is grammatically correct, but sounds slightly unnatural. A more natural phrasing would reflect a more active voice and be more direct.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Daži lietotāji, kurus vēlaties iesaistīt, nevar piekļūt telpai: {{users}}

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Alguns utilizadores que quer mencionar não têm acesso à sala: {{users}}' is not a perfect translation. 'quer mencionar' is a bit awkward. A more natural phrasing would be 'que pretende mencionar' or 'que você deseja mencionar'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Alguns utilizadores que pretende mencionar não têm acesso à sala: {{users}}

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The sentence structure is slightly awkward. Using 'pe care doriți să-i menționați' can be improved for better flow.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Unii utilizatori pe care doriți să-i menționați nu au acces în sală: {{users}}

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation "ඔබට සඳහන් කිරීමට වුවමනා ඇතැම් අයට කාමරය වෙත ප්‍රවේශය නැත: {{users}}" is a bit literal and awkward. A more natural phrasing would convey the meaning more clearly.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ඔබ සඳහන් කරන සමහර χρήστες කාමරයට ඇතුළුවීමට අවසර නැත: {{users}}

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The word 'ය' is repeated unnecessarily in 'ඔබට සඳහන් කිරීමට වුවමනා ඇතැම්'.

The Serbian translation 'Неки корисници које желите поменути немају приступ соби: {{users}}' is technically correct but sounds slightly unnatural. A more natural phrasing would be 'Неки од корисника које желите да поменете немају приступ соби: {{users}}' or 'Неки корисници које желите да споменете немају приступ соби: {{users}}'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Неки од корисника које желите да поменете немају приступ соби: {{users}} or Неки корисници које желите да споменете немају приступ соби: {{users}}

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Một số người dùng mà bạn muốn đề cập đến không có quyền truy cập vào phòng: {{users}}' is a literal translation and sounds awkward in Vietnamese. A more natural phrasing would be 'Một số người dùng mà bạn muốn nhắc đến không có quyền truy cập vào phòng: {{users}}' or 'Một số người dùng mà bạn muốn đề cập không có quyền truy cập vào phòng: {{users}}'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Một số người dùng mà bạn muốn nhắc đến không có quyền truy cập vào phòng: {{users}}

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The phrase "Some users whom you want to mention" is not perfectly conveyed. A more natural and common phrasing in Chinese would be "您想提及的用户". "部分用户" implies a subset, which might not be the intended meaning.  The English implies all users you *want* to mention, regardless of whether they are a subset of all users.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: 您想提及的用户没有房间访问权限：{{users}}
